<p>GDP growth: 4.7% GDP: $246bn (PPP: $300bn) Inflation: 3.2% Population: 17.4m GDP per head: $14,150 (PPP: $17,240)</p>

<p>The ruling Coalición, an alliance between the right-wing Unión Demócrata Independiente and President Sebastián Piñera's Renovación Nacional, is creaking as policy swings towards the centre in response to declining ratings and social protest. It will survive, but major initiatives, such as a flagship labour reform, will be pushed back. Earthquake reconstruction will divert some fiscal resources, but Chile's robust economy will shrug off the expense and manage a tidy rate of growth.</p>

